      <description>Geoffrey Lamarque, MBE, served in the Indian Civil Service between 1937
            and 1947. Patricia Lamarque married Geoffrey Lamarque in 1945 and moved to India where
            he worked in the Indian Civil Service and for the Government of India at New Delhi and
            Calcutta. After Indian independence in 1947, when her husband became a career diplomat,
            the Lamarques worked and lived in Melbourne, Karachi, Canada, Nigeria and
            Rome.</description>
